text_Basalt: slightly smooth, single color and mostly singe stone; smooth-ish when broken, would feel like the side of a boulder, mostly dark in color, although one is light gray in photo above;
text_Gabbro: Gabbro is junky and coarse, not smooth; it's appearance is common and makes me think of construction sites and gravel driveways; it isn't smooth and looks like a faded blend of more than one sort of stone/mineral amalgamation; it's not pretty

text_Pegmatite: pegmatite has pretty embeds of other stones, usually striking in color and thickness; feels and looks like a boulder was broken open; not entirely smooth, but not coarse like gravel or peridotite; I would pick this rock up to examine it. the embeds are more significant than the peridotite
text_Peridotite: slightly interesting with tiny pinpricks of color; sort of rough, almost like gravel; has bumpy texture; somewhat interesting up close, but doesn't appear as nice or interesting as pegmatite; embeds are quite small.

text_Basalt: kind of plain with slight smoothness when broken. color is usually fairly uniform and singly colored; slightly nicer than gabbro;
text_Andesite: andesite is speckled; has embeds as if small stones or chips embedded in a concrete mixtures, but some of the concrete mixture can be black with light specks, like tweed. thinking of rice krispie treats. speckled/spotted appearance gives interest.

text_Peridotite: rather coarse unassuming base stone with pin pricks or small embeds of other rocks or mineral deposits; not that pretty but still interesting, at least more than plain gravel. no real angular edges, just roundish with bumpiness

text_Andesite: speckled, often pretty well contrasted colors, usually of grays, blacks and whites, but some of the embeds can be varied; interesting b/c of speckled appearance; base stone often gray but can be black. these don't look very smooth.
text_Peridotite: irregularly shaped stones with a coarse texture mostly; has tiny embeds or pin pricks of colors from other stones or minerals somewhat embedded; may be pretty when wet and examined up close, otherwise looks unassuming; some embeds look pretty, but mostly are small.
